{"title_page": "Frederik R\u00f8nnow", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name  = Frederik R\u00f8nnow\n| image       = FrederikR\u00f6nnow.jpg\n| caption     = R\u00f8nnow in 2019\n| fullname    = Frederik Riis R\u00f8nnow\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1992|8|4|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Horsens]], Denmark\n| height      = 1.90 m<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tournament.fifadata.com/documents/FWC/2018/pdf/FWC_2018_SQUADLISTS.PDF |title=2018 FIFA World Cup Russia \u2013 List of Players |website=FIFA.com |publisher=F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Football Association |format=PDF |date=4 June 2018 |access-date=19 June 2018}}</ref>\n| currentclub = [[Eintracht Frankfurt]]\n| clubnumber  = 32\n| position    = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = Stensballe IK\n| youthyears2 = |youthclubs2 = [[AC Horsens]]\n| years1      = 2010\u20132015 |clubs1 = [[AC Horsens]]          |caps1 = 56 |goals1 = 0\n| years2      = 2013\u20132014 |clubs2 = \u2192 [[Esbjerg fB]] (loan) |caps2 = 18 |goals2 = 0\n| years3      = 2015\u20132018 |clubs3 = [[Br\u00f8ndby IF|Br\u00f8ndby]]  |caps3 = 99 |goals3 = 0\n| years4      = 2018\u2013     |clubs4 = [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] |caps4 = 10 |goals4 = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 2010      |nationalteam1 = [[Denmark national under-18 football team|Denmark U18]] |nationalcaps1 = 4  |nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2010\u20132011 |nationalteam2 = [[Denmark national under-19 football team|Denmark U19]] |nationalcaps2 = 3  |nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2012      |nationalteam3 = [[Denmark national under-20 football team|Denmark U20]] |nationalcaps3 = 1  |nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalyears4 = 2012\u20132015 |nationalteam4 = [[Denmark national under-21 football team|Denmark U21]] |nationalcaps4 = 14 |nationalgoals4 = 0\n| nationalyears5 = 2016\u2013     |nationalteam5 = [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]]              |nationalcaps5 = 7  |nationalgoals5 = 0\n| club-update = 12 December 2019\n| ntupdate    = 16 June 2018\n}}\n'''Frederik Riis R\u00f8nnow''' ({{IPA-da|\u02c8f\u0281e\u00f0\u02c0\u0281ek \u02c8\u0281i\u02c0s \u02c8\u0281\u0276n\u028cw}}; born 4 August 1992) is a Danish professional [[association football]] player in the [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] position, who currently plays for [[Eintracht Frankfurt]].\n\n==Career==\n===Early career===\nR\u00f8nnow started his career as a youth player at [[Horsens]] club Stensballe IK before he at the age of 16 years transferred to [[AC Horsens]]. He made his first team debut on 7 September 2011 in a cup match against [[Holstebro Boldklub|Holstebro]], a game Horsens won 5-0.\n\nAlready being the first choice goalkeeper for the [[Denmark national under-21 football team|Danish U-21 team]], and having been awarded the Horsens [[player of the year award]] for the 2012/13 season,<ref>[http://www.bold.dk/nyt/Frederik-Roennow-aarets-spiller-i-Horsens Frederik R\u00f8nnow \u00e5rets spiller i Horsens]</ref> R\u00f8nnow's agent, former Danish international [[John Siveb\u00e6k]], expressed his reluctance for his client to be playing in the [[Danish 1st Division]] following Horsens relegation from the [[Danish Superliga]].<ref>[http://www.bold.dk/nyt/Roennow-agent-Ikke-optimalt-med-1-div R\u00f8nnow-agent: Ikke optimalt med 1. div.]</ref> As a consequence, on 5 July R\u00f8nnow moved to Superliga club Esbjerg on a year long loan<ref>[http://www.efb.dk/?type=nyhed&id=792&popup= EfB lejer Frederik R\u00f8nnow i AC Horsens]</ref> following the departure of [[Luk\u00e1\u0161 Hr\u00e1deck\u00fd]] to league rivals [[Br\u00f8ndby IF]].\n\n===Br\u00f8ndby===\nOn 10 May 2018 he played as Br\u00f8ndby beat [[Silkeborg IF]] 3&ndash;1 in the [[2017-18 Danish Cup]] final.<ref>http://sport.tv2.dk/fodbold/2018-05-10-broendby-er-pokalmester-ender-ti-aars-pokaltoerke</ref><ref>https://www.eurosport.com/football/dbu-pokalen/2017-2018/live-brondby-if-silkeborg-if_mtc954491/live.shtml</ref>\n\n===Eintracht Frankfurt===\nIn April 2018 it was announced that R\u00f8nnow would join [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] in July 2018, again mirroring the movements of Hr\u00e1deck\u00fd.<ref>https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/lukas-hradecky-eintracht-frankfurt-goalkeeper-departure-kovac-frederik-ronnow-478579.jsp</ref> R\u00f8nnow made his debut in the [[2018 DFL-Supercup|German Super Cup]] on 12 August 2018.<ref name=\"FCB gewinnt Supercup - Lewandowski macht den Unterschied\">{{cite web |title=FCB gewinnt Supercup - Lewandowski macht den Unterschied |url=http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/startseite/d-supercup-fb-1/2018/1/4213948/spielanalyse_eintracht-frankfurt-32_bayern-muenchen-14.html |website=kicker.de |publisher=kicker |accessdate=9 February 2019 |language=German}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nAfter playing for several Danish youth teams, he was called up to represent the [[Denmark national football team|Senior]] team on 9 March 2016 by the new head coach [[\u00c5ge Hareide]], for the friendly matches against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]] and [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.twtd.co.uk/ipswich-town-news/29225/knudsen-in-danish-squad|title=Knudsen in Danish Squad|publisher=twtd.co.uk|date=9 March 2016 |accessdate=10 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2018 he was named in Denmark's [[Denmark national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in [[Russia]].<ref>http://www.goal.com/en-gb/amp/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club statistics===\n{{updated|match played on 12 December 2019.}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" Style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club!!rowspan=\"2\"|Season!!colspan=\"3\"|League!!colspan=\"2\"|Cup!!colspan=\"2\"|Continental!!colspan=\"2\"|Other!!colspan=\"2\"|Total!!rowspan=\"2\"|{{Tooltip|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!